<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900713-0017</DOCNO><DOCID>900713-0017.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Apple Computer Inc.:   Concern Will Let Bitstream   Sell Its Font Technology</HL><DATE>07/13/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B8</SO><CO>   AAPL ADBE</CO><IN>COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)</IN><LP>   Apple Computer Inc., Cupertino, Calif., lobbed anothervolley in the font wars by agreeing to allow Bitstream Inc.to sell Apple's font technology, programs that determine howcomputers represent text on computer screens and printers.   Apple is trying to win converts to its font software fromAdobe Systems Inc., the leader of the market for fontsoftware, which is essential in desktop publishing. Apple,one of Adobe's biggest customers, caused a stir in thepersonal-computer world last year when it and Microsoft Corp.announced they would offer a product rivaling Adobe'sPostscript font software.</LP><TEXT>   Apple's agreement with Bitstream will allow Bitstream tolicense Apple's font product, called TrueType, to hundredsmanufacturers and software developers. Bitstream, aCambridge, Mass., software concern, now licenses fonts tomore than 370 companies around the world. Apple said it hopesto &quot;extend the reach&quot; of TrueType in the personal-computermarket.</TEXT></DOC>